# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1D radially symmetric solution used to compare results to 2d problem
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
This is the results of using 1d Clawpack to solve the radially symmetric
wave equation.

        - Initial pulse : presssure = H(r),

where r = abs(x-2.5).

Data file for input parameters  : claw1ez.data

Data file for physical parameters : setprob.data (same as 2d problem)

Riemann solver : rp1.f

Initial conditions are in : qinit.f

Source term (metric term for radially symmetric case) : src1.f

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
This version was compiled using gcc 3.4, on an Intel P4, under Linux.

To compile a new version, download 1d library files at

                   http:://www.amath.washington.edu/~claw

Set environment variable "CLAW", and compile using 'gmake'.

